23/05/2003
OHRID, Macedonia -- The prime ministers of Macedonia, Serbia-Montenegro, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Croatia, Romania and Albania adopted a common platform on border security Thursday (22 May), aimed at co-ordinating efforts to bring border management in the Balkans into line with EU standards. 
Meeting in Ohrid, the Balkan leaders reiterated their commitment to fighting organised crime and the illegal trafficking of weapons and people. 
Macedonian Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva held bilateral meetings with counterparts from Bulgaria and Serbia-Montenegro. 
The talks resulted in the signing of a co-operation memorandum between Macedonia and Bulgaria in the field of EU integration, as well as the opening of new four border crossings with Serbia-Montenegro. 
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 23/05/03; MIA, A1 TV, Makfax - 22/05/03)
